            <additions>
              <note type="proofreader-note">N.B., folio location may not be available for some items below.</note>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <p>A later hand has renumbered the quires with letters only.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <p>Many lessons have been noted by later hands on the margins, some of the latter being written with green paint.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition3" n="3">
                  <p>A reader called<listPerson>
                      <person>
                        <persName>Salībā</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="syr">ܨܠܝܒܐ ܚܛܝܐ</persName>
                      </person>
                    </listPerson>has written his name on the margin of foll.<locus from="17b" to="17b">17 b</locus>and<locus from="18b" to="18b">18 b</locus>.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition4" n="4">
                  <p>Foll.<locus from="154b" to="154b">154 b</locus>and<locus from="156a" to="156a">156 a</locus>have been retouched at a later date, and one half of<locus from="155" to="155">fol. 155</locus>has been supplied on<material>paper</material>about the end of the<date notBefore="1000" notAfter="1100">11th century</date>.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition5" n="5" syriaca-tags="scribal-colophon">
                  <label>Colophon</label>
                  <locus from="157b" to="157b"/>
                  <p>On fol. 157 b there is a note, in the handwriting of the scribe, stating that this book was collated by<persName>Kashīsh</persName>, the Arab, priest of the district called<placeName>Nahrā dě-Kastra</placeName>, along with his syncelli<persName ref="syr">John bar Daniel</persName>, the Arab, and<persName>John</persName>, the deacon, of<placeName xml:lang="syr">ܐܘܢܡܪܐ</placeName>, who was also of Arab race.</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܢܥܒܕ ܡܪܢ ܪ̈ܚܡܐ ܘܚܢܢܐ ܒܝܘܡܐ ܪܒܐ ܕܡܐܬܝܬܗ܆ ܥܠ ܟܠ ܡܢ ܕܦܚܡ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܘܗ̣ܘܐ ܠܗ ܫܩ̣ܠ ܛܥܢܐ ܡܛܠ ܦܘܚܡܗ ܕܡܢ ܛܥܘ̈ܢܐ. ܦܚܡܘܗܝ ܕܝܢ ܒܫܩ̣ܠ ܛܥܢܐ ܣܓܝܐܐ̣. ܡܪܝ ܩܫܝܫ ܛܝܝܐ ܩܫܝܫܐ ܕܢܗܪܐ ܕܩܣܛܪܐ̣. ܥܡ ܒ̈ܢܝ ܩܠܝܬܗ ܕܝܨܦܘ ܥܡܗ. ܡܪܝ ܝܘܚܢܢ ܛܝܝܐ ܒܪ ܕܢܝܐܝܠ̣. ܘܡܪܝ ܝܘܚܢܢ ܫܡܫܐ ܕܡܢ ܐܘܢܡܪܐ̇. ܥܪܒܝܐ ܕܝܢ ܐܝܘܘܗܝ ܒܓܢܣܗ. ܕܐܠܗܐ ܗ̇ܘ ܕܡܛܠ ܫܡܗ ܝܨܦܘ ܡܛܠ ܦܘܚܡܗ ܕܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ̣. ܗ̣ܘ ܢܬܠ ܠܗܘܢ ܦܘܪܥܢܐ ܛܒ̇ܐ̣ ܘ܏ܫ</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition6" n="6" syriaca-tags="scribal-colophon">
                  <label>Colophon</label>
                  <locus from="157b" to="157b"/>
                  <p>The name of the scribe appears to have been<persName>David</persName>, for under<ref target="#addition5">the above note</ref>we read:</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܒܡܪܢ ܣܒܪܢ ܟܠ ܡܢ ܕܩ̇ܪܐ ܢܨܠܐ [ܥܠ add] ܕܘܝܕ ܚܛܝܐ. . ܕܥܠ ܛܘܢܢܐ  ܕܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ. ܘ.</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
              </list>
